'''Addi''' ([[Tigrinya language|Tigrinya]] ዓዲ ''ʿĀddī'', [[Tigre language|Tigre]], [[Ge'ez language|Ge'ez]] ዓድ ''ʿĀd'') is a Tigrinya term meaning "village" derived from the Ge'ez word "Ad" meaning "son." The word can be found in many village and city names in [[Tigray Region]], [[Ethiopia]] and Tigre and Tigrinya-speaking Eritrea.{{Fact|date=November 2008}}

