{{Infobox diocese | jurisdiction = Eparchy<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese --> | name = Segheneyti | latin = Eparchia Segheneitensis | local = <!-- Name in the native language --> | image = | image_size = 200px | image_alt = | caption = <!---- Locations ----> | country = [[Eritrea]] | territory = | province = [[Eritrean Catholic Archeparchy of Asmara|Asmara]] | coordinates = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> <!---- Statistics ----> | area_km2 = 29,499<!-- Area in square kilometers, automatically converted --> | population = 850,000 | population_as_of = 2012 | catholics = 35,557<!-- Number of Catholics in the diocese --> | catholics_percent = 4.2 | parishes = 33<!-- Number of parishes in the diocese --> | churches = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese --> | congregations = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese --> | schools = <!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese --> | members = <!-- Number of members in the diocese --> <!---- Information ----> | denomination = [[Eritrean Catholic Church]] | rite = [[Alexandrian Rite]] | established = 24 February 2012 ({{age|2012|2|24}} years ago) | cathedral = Cathedral of St. Michael the Archangel | cocathedral = | patron = | priests = <!-- Number of priests in the diocese --> <!---- Current leadership ----> | pope = {{Incumbent pope}} | bishop = [[Fikremariam Hagos Tsalim]] | bishop_title = Bishop | coadjutor = | auxiliary_bishops = | vicar_general = | emeritus_bishops = <!---- Map ----> | map = | map_alt = | map_caption = <!---- Website ----> | website = | footnotes = }}
The '''Eritrean Catholic Eparchy of Segheneyti''' ({{lang-la|Eparchia Segheneitensis}}) is a [[Eritrean Catholic Church|Catholic]] [[eparchy]] located in the town of [[Segheneyti]] in [[Eritrea]]. It is a part of the [[ecclesiastical province]] of [[Eritrean Catholic Archeparchy of Asmara|Asmara]]. The eparchy follows the [[Alexandrian Rite]], and has a cathedral of [[Michael (archangel)|Saint Michael the Archangel]].
== History == On 24 February 2012, [[Pope Benedict XVI]] established the Eparchy of Segheneyti from the [[Eritrean Catholic Archeparchy of Asmara|Eparchy of Asmara]] and it became [[suffragan]] of the [[Ethiopian Catholic Archeparchy of Addis Abeba]].<ref name=hierarchy>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dsegh.html|title=Eparchy of Segheneyti (Ethiopian)|publisher=Catholic-Hierarchy|accessdate=2013-06-18}}</ref><ref name=GCatholic>{{cite web|url=http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/segh0.htm|title=Ethiopic Diocese of Segheneyti|publisher=Giga Catholic|accessdate=2013-06-18}}</ref>
With the establishment of the autonomous ''[[sui iuris]]'' [[Eritrean Catholic Church]] by [[Pope Francis]] in January 2015, the Eparchy of Segheneyti became a suffragan the [[Eritrean Catholic Archeparchy of Asmara]].<ref name="Eritrean Catholic Church">{{cite web | url=http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/de/bollettino/pubblico/2015/01/19/0048/00098.html | title=Erezione della Chiesa Metropolitana sui iuris eritrea e nomina del primo Metropolita | publisher=[[Holy See Press Office]] | date=January 19, 2015 | accessdate=January 19, 2015}}</ref>
== Ordinaries == * Fikremariam Hagos Tsalim (24 Feb 2012–present)
