[[File:Flag of Akershus.svg|thumb|Akershus Flag]]
The '''flag of Akershus''' represents [[Akershus]] county, [[Norway]]. Designed by Finn Fagerli, it was approved by Royal Resolution on 11 December 1987. The flag is a banner of the [[Coat of arms of Akershus]] which is a silver [[Crow-stepped gable|step-gable]] on a blue field. It is rare among Norwegian flags in being square. The design is a reference to [[Akershus Fortress|Akershus Castle]] where several of the buildings feature such gables. The castle was the seat of the governor of Akershus [[Amt (country subdivision)|Amt]], the predecessor of today's county.

