'''Gnällbältet''', Swedish, "The whining belt", is an informal name referring to a [[geographic belt]] in central [[Sweden]] where the [[dialect]]s have certain features in common, mostly extensive usage of the [[schwa]] sound. The belt consists of [[Västmanland]], [[Närke]] and the western parts of [[Södermanland]], but are characteristic to a much reduced degree throughout the [[Mälaren Valley]].

